# Generated artifacts.
#
# NOTE: these patterns are ANCHORED with a leading slash so they match only at the
# repo root. An unanchored `data/` or `models/` matches a directory of that name at
# ANY depth, which would also swallow src/data/ and src/models/ and silently
# untrack the source tree.
#
# Comments must be on their own line -- git does not support trailing comments, so
# `/data/   # features` would be read as a pattern containing spaces and a hash.

# extracted features (huge)
/data/
# training outputs
/runs/
# downloaded model weights (e.g. BLEURT)
/models/
# generated experiment scripts
/scripts/generated/

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.pytest_cache/
*.egg-info/
.venv/

# OS
.DS_Store

CONTRIBUTING.md